parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle may not be properly protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident
despite the severity of the impact; seatbelts may not engage or may malfunction; warning lights or messages may appear on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seatbelts can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle may not be properly restrained in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seatbelts may not engage or may malfunction; seatbelts may be improperly installed or may be damaged; warning lights or messages may appear on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the seatbelt system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of airbag sensors can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, or the deployment of airbags in non-accident situations, which can cause injuries or distractions.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights or messages may appear on the dashboard; airbags may deploy unnecessarily; airbags may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop or slow down in time.
symptoms: Brakes may not engage or may malfunction; vehicle may not stop or slow down when brakes are applied; warning lights or messages may appear on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: smoke or flames from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the PCV valve can cause engine pressure to build up, leading to broken gaskets, vacuum leaks, misfiring, and loss of power, which can be a safety issue.
Failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: high engine temperature warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clutch or transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: clutch pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the Stabilitrak system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: inability to accelerate or maneuver the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission manufacturing defect can cause the vehicle to enter limp mode, leaving the driver stranded and unable to accelerate or maneuver the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
Turbo failure can cause a lack of power to the vehicle when accelerating, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the instrument panel and screen to malfunction, leading to a loss of critical vehicle information and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
Poor acceleration and sticking accelerator can cause the vehicle to accelerate unpredictably, leading to accidents or injuries.
Unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents or injuries, especially when the vehicle is in park or stationary.
